n><span> : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Symbolic abstraction over integers.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-S_range\"><a href=\"#module-S_range\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"S_range/index.html\">S_range</a></span><span> : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Symbolic abstractions over ranges.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-S_map\"><a href=\"#module-S_map\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"S_map/index.html\">S_map</a></span><span> : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>A symbolic map abstraction. The main function of the <a href=\"S_map/S/module-type-S/index.html\" title=\"S.S\">symbolic map module type</a> is <a href=\"S_map/S/module-type-S/index.html#val-find_opt\" title=\"S.S.find_opt\"><code>find_opt</code></a>, which allows symbolically looking up a key in the map (possibly branching), and returns the value at that key if any, along with the key to be used for future <i>concrete</i> operations on the map.</p></div></div>"}